  "texts": [
    "In the era of the commercialisation of chatbots exploiting LLMs, it is high time for policymakers and the legal system to find the right tools to prevent discriminatory outputs, starting with streamlining the process of training and the choice of data.",
    "Secondly, another concern that arises is whether the information fed to LLMs via large datasets used for training can be used at all for such a purpose.",
    "At least two problems can be flagged under this perspective.",
    "On the one hand, large datasets harbour a real risk of exposure of the personal data of unknowing individuals.",
    "It has been proven that, under some conditions, it is possible to reverse engineer data present in large datasets used for training in order to extract personal data referring to identifiable individuals."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}